The paper focuses on similarity search in large-scale multimedia retrieval applications, which suggests that it could belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) or information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The use of supervised hashing and discriminative hash function learning also suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of "data reconstruction" suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
